{"cursor":"4188","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox artist\n| name = Achilles Painter image = Oidipous Sphinx Staatliche Antikensammlungen\n| SL474.jpg image_size = 275px alt = caption = Oedipus and the Sphinx, amphora\n| by the Achilles Painter, located in the Staatliche Antikensammlungen, Berlin,\n| Number SL 474. birth_name = Unknown. Name assigned by Beazley after a theme of\n| Achilles painted on a Lekythos in the Vatican Museums. birth_date = Before 470\n| BC birth_place = Probably Athens death_date = About 425 BC death_place =\n| nationality = Greek spouse = field = Pottery-making, vase painting. He took\n| over the Berlin Painter's workshop. training = Berlin Painter's workshp\n| movement = red-figure style, white ground technique works = Over 200 vases,\n| mainly funerary lekythoi patrons = influenced by = Berlin Painter influenced =\n| Phiale Painter and other students in his workshop awards = elected = website =\n| bgcolour =\n}}\n\nThe 'Achilles Painter', was a vase-painter active ca. 470-425 BC. His name vase\nis an amphora, Vatican 16571, in the Vatican museums depicting Achilles. The\namphora is dated 450-445 BC. An armed and armored Achilles gazes pensively to\nthe right with one hand on his hip. The other hand holds a spear. On the\nopposite surface a woman performs libation.\n\nSir John Beazley attributed over 200 vases to his hand, the largest share being\nred-figure and white-ground lekythoi. In his middle phase (ca. 450-445 BC), he\ndecorates more open forms. The Achilles Painter was a late pupil of the Berlin\nPainter. J.D. Beazley, Attic Red-figure Vase-painters (2nd ed., Oxford,\n1963) 986.\n\nThe Phiale Painter became the Achilles Painter's most prominent student after\nhe assumed the Berlin Painter's workshop. Almost a dozen other recognizable\npainters passed through the Achilles Painter's workshop as well. Notable\npainters include the Westreenen Painter, the Persephone Painter, the Clio\nPainter, Loeb Painter, and the Dwarf Painter. The Kleophon Painter, the\nSabouroff Painter, and the Painter of Munich 2335 all spent time at the\nworkshop as well.\n","linknr":217,"url":"Achilles_Painter","recorded":1375071661,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Achilles_Painter&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Achilles_Painter&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Oidipous_Sphinx_Staatliche_Antikensammlungen_SL474.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Oidipous_Sphinx_Staatliche_Antikensammlungen_SL474.jpg/275px-Oidipous_Sphinx_Staatliche_Antikensammlungen_SL474.jpg","/wiki/Oedipus","/wiki/Sphinx","/wiki/Amphora","/wiki/Staatliche_Antikensammlungen","/wiki/Berlin","/wiki/Berlin_Painter","/wiki/Red-figure","/wiki/White_ground_technique","/wiki/Lekythos","/wiki/Berlin_Painter","/wiki/Phiale_Painter","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Achilles_Painter","/wiki/Pottery_of_ancient_Greece","/wiki/Name_vase","/wiki/Amphora","/wiki/Vatican_museums","#cite_note-1","/wiki/John_Beazley","/wiki/Red-figure","/wiki/White_ground_technique","/wiki/Lekythos","/wiki/Berlin_Painter","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Phiale_Painter","/wi